    <question>
        <stimulus>"The corrupt alliance between business and politics threatens the very foundation of our democracy... We must choose between a government by corporations and a government by the people."
- Robert La Follette, 1912 Presidential Campaign Speech</stimulus>
        <prompt>Which Progressive Era reform most directly addressed this concern?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The Federal Trade Commission</option>
            <option letter="b">The Pure Food and Drug Act</option>
            <option letter="c">The Federal Reserve Act</option>
            <option letter="d">The Adamson Act</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Federal Trade Commission was created to regulate business practices and prevent corrupt alliances between business and politics, addressing La Follette's concerns.</explanation>
